channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Former tabloid executive continues testimony in Trump trial
item.description: Donald Trump's New York hush money criminal trial continues Tuesday. Follow here for the latest live news updates, analysis and more.

item.title: DOJ announces $139M settlement with Larry Nassar victims for claims of FBI misconduct
item.description: Larry Nassar's victims have reached a $138.7 million settlement deal with the Justice Department to resolve their claims of wrongdoing against the FBI

item.title: Protests at Columbia and other schools escalate
item.description: Officials at Columbia University, facing surging tensions on campus, have taken steps to try to address students' concerns over safety and freedom of expression.

item.title: Biden will speak at Morehouse commencement, an election-year spotlight in front of Black voters
item.description: President Joe Biden will be the commencement speaker for Georgia's Morehouse College and at West Point next month

item.title: Devastation in Gaza as Israel wages war on Hamas
item.description: A grave with nearly 300 bodies has been uncovered at a hospital in the southern Gaza city of Khan Younis, Gaza Civil Defense workers said, following the withdrawal of Israeli forces from the area earlier this month.

item.title: Ship that hit bridge was 'unseaworthy' when it left, city claims
item.description: The Dali, the container ship that crashed into the Francis Scott Key Bridge in March, set sail despite its "unseaworthy" conditions, according to a Monday court filing.

item.title: April 22, 2024 - Israel-Hamas war
item.description: The head of the Israeli military's intelligence branch has resigned, becoming the first senior military figure to resign over October 7 failings.

item.title: Trump trial: Publisher describes secret catch-and-kill arrangement for 2016 election
item.description: Follow the latest developments in former President Donald Trump's criminal hush money trial in New York.

item.title: April 22, 2024 - Protests at Columbia and other schools escalate
item.description: Heightened tensions around pro-Palestinian protests on the campus of Columbia University have led the school to go all-virtual on Monday. The protests are now in their sixth day.

item.title: Police search for ex-cop who allegedly killed ex-wife, girlfriend; abducted child
item.description: West Richland Washington Police are asking for the public's help in locating a murder suspect they say is "armed" and "dangerous."
